{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Context\n\nWhen the plan-review claim gate re-fires on a CONTAINER ticket (epic/story with children) that is\nmid-execution, it reviews the plan as if FRESH — blind to which children are already delivered. It\nthen re-litigates acceptance criteria already shipped by closed+attested children: false BLOCKs and\ncoaching to tighten AC that is done, plus a slow whole-context review of settled work.\n\nRe-fires are legitimate but infrequent — a paused epic reopened (ADR 0009 invalidates an\nattestation signed before the reopen), or a material course-correction to the epic plan\n(material-fingerprint invalidation). The claim CASCADE is not the driver (it only fires while the\nparent is `open`). Code-drift invalidation is INTENTIONAL and unchanged (a container's plan is\nreviewed against codebase state — G6 runs at container scope): this epic changes only what a\nre-fired review DOES, not when it fires.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A re-fired container review does not re-litigate delivered AC: findings limited to a\n  delivered-now child's plan-semantics are dropped; delivered-functionality, cross-sibling, and\n  severe/security/contract findings are always preserved.\n- Suppression is deterministic in Pass-3, keyed on VERIFIED delivery (completion attestation or\n  in-epic supersede), never on bare `closed` status; force-closed/abandoned children stay in scope.\n- No change to WHEN a review is invalidated (code-drift stays), no `close`-op change, no new\n  attestation kind.\n\n## What we build\n\nA deterministic Pass-3 \"completion floor\" (third floor beside the novelty floor ADR 0008 and the\ndrift-refresh path ADR 0002), fed by a separate `plan_review_completion` Pass-2 sub-call (mirroring\n`plan_review_novelty`) that answers three atomic orthogonal sub-questions per finding: ATTRIBUTION\n(which closed child), CONTAINMENT (limited vs spans open), LAYER (plan-semantics vs\ndelivered-functionality). Pass-1 stays completion-blind (full recall); the coach is unchanged.\n\n## Scope\n\n- IN: the Pass-2 completion sub-call + three sub-questions; the Pass-3 completion floor + config\n  evidence-gate + priority floor; the delivered-now predicate (attestation reuse + in-epic sibling\n  supersede); sidecar recording; calibration gold-set + tests.\n- OUT (deferred, separate epics): partial-completion attestation for in-progress children; a\n  structured `resolution` enum on `close`; the sidecar re-injection queue; an optional second LAYER\n  binary. In-progress children stay FULLY in scope in v1.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\n- (a) Exempt epics from the claim gate — REJECTED: discards the container security review ADR 0016\n  added (a container epic that stands up infrastructure would go unreviewed).\n- (b) Completion-aware container review — CHOSEN; hybrid = (b) + keying on VERIFIED delivery\n  (completion attestation) + in-epic sibling supersede.\n- Decomposition-drift-only freshness (never invalidate a container on code drift) — REJECTED:\n  code-drift invalidation is intentional; a container's plan IS reviewed vs codebase state (G6 runs\n  at container scope).\n- A single composite predicate instead of three sub-questions — REJECTED: attribution / containment\n  / layer are orthogonal (identity / spatial scope / artifact layer); folding them loses the\n  distinctions and re-couples model category + severity error.\n- Hide delivered children / review only open children — REJECTED: blinds coherence + security to\n  delivered<->open interactions; we FREEZE delivered children as visible context, not hide them.\n- Tag- or progress-note-based suppression — REJECTED: unsigned + gameable (prompt-injection surface\n  into a security-sensitive gate); we key on the signed completion attestation.\n- Run the completion-verifier to drive scoping — REJECTED: FAIL-by-construction mid-flight + signing\n  ambiguity (needs a third attestation kind); we READ the attestation closed children already carry.\n- Reuse the novelty sub-answer mechanism (add the three completion questions to NOVELTY_SUBANSWERS)\n  instead of a parallel sub-call — REJECTED: completion keys on a DIFFERENT context input (the\n  delivered-children manifest) than novelty (prior findings), so a separate sub-call preserves the\n  Pass-1 independence invariant by construction; they share the kernel sub-answer machinery, not context.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] Brainstorm + decision recorded (a vs b vs hybrid) — DONE: decision comment + the '## Alternatives considered' section + the completion session log; option (b)/hybrid chosen with rationale.\n- [ ] A separate `plan_review_completion` Pass-2 sub-call (mirroring `plan_review_novelty`) emits, per finding, {attribution, containment, layer} with fail-safe values (insufficient/n/a/spans-open/delivered-functionality all keep).\n- [ ] Pass-3 completion floor drops a finding iff attribution=delivered-now-child AND containment=limited AND layer=plan-semantics AND priority<floor AND criterion not in {security,contract}; gated behind an evidence-gate flag + configurable priority floor (mirroring the novelty floor).\n- [ ] `delivered-now` = valid completion attestation (validity-on-read, reusing the `_child_closure_findings` predicate) OR superseded by a sibling under the same parent; force-closed/abandoned/in-progress children are NOT delivered and stay in scope.\n- [ ] Drops recorded to the REVIEW_RESULT sidecar (joinable, observable) and recomputed every run (a reopened/un-delivered child auto-resurfaces its findings).\n- [ ] A durable ADR (`docs/adr/0020-completion-aware-container-plan-review.md`) codifies the new contracts (sub-call schema + closed enums, delivered-now predicate, completion floor + config, sidecar drop_reason) — inline AC + session log are not the durable record.\n- [ ] Tests: a partially-complete epic review drops delivered plan-semantics findings yet preserves (a) a delivered child's delivered-functionality/security finding, (b) a finding spanning an open sibling, (c) all findings on a force-closed child; plus a calibration gold-set of must-never-suppress cases."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782975265261009001,"uuid":"869b7d9c-defc-414e-af40-39082866a4fc"}